Python or stick with proprietary tools like SPSS?

00:09:54.880 --> 00:10:00.640
To help, I turn your attention to the Andre Walker hair typing system.

00:10:01.520 --> 00:10:08.400
So, hairstylist and businessman Andre Walker is known for maintaining Oprah Winfrey's hair

00:10:08.400 --> 00:10:09.440
for decades.

00:10:10.159 --> 00:10:13.679
So, if he did Oprah's hair clearly, he got something going on.

00:10:14.719 --> 00:10:18.320
He's also known for creating Halle Berry's pixie cut.

00:10:19.520 --> 00:10:25.200
In 1997, he created a numerical grading system for human hair types.

00:10:25.280 --> 00:10:31.280
The Andre Walker hair typing system classifies Afro-textured hair as type four.

00:10:32.960 --> 00:10:37.840
There are other types of hair defined as one for straight hair, type two for wavy, and

00:10:37.840 --> 00:10:45.760
type three for curly, with letters A, B, and C used to indicate the degree of coil variation

00:10:45.760 --> 00:10:46.880
in each type.

