00:13:38.559 --> 00:13:44.159
Putting this all together, I want to introduce you to a few organizations that are doing

00:13:44.159 --> 00:13:44.719
the work.

00:13:46.400 --> 00:13:52.320
These organizations are using their data science skills to positively impact Black and brown

00:13:52.320 --> 00:13:54.479
people's lives worldwide.

00:13:55.679 --> 00:13:58.880
The first organization is Data for Black Lives.

00:14:00.880 --> 00:14:06.880
Data for Black Lives is a movement of activists, organizers, and scientists committed to using

00:14:07.840 --> 00:14:13.119
data to create concrete and measurable change in the lives of Black people.

00:14:14.400 --> 00:14:21.119
Through their research, advocacy, and community building, they support the vital work of grassroots

00:14:21.119 --> 00:14:26.719
racial justice organizations to challenge discriminatory uses of data and algorithms

00:14:26.719 --> 00:14:27.760
across systems.

00:14:29.119 --> 00:14:34.960
They have a national network of about 20,000 scientists, activists, those who are building

00:14:34.960 --> 00:14:42.559
a future where data and technology is used for good rather than instruments of oppression

00:14:42.559 --> 00:14:43.520
in the Black community.

00:14:44.960 --> 00:14:50.880
The second organization is the Algorithmic Justice League, and this organization leads

00:14:50.880 --> 00:14:55.919
a cultural movement towards equitable and accountable artificial intelligence.

00:14:56.799 --> 00:15:03.440
Their mission is to raise public awareness about the impacts of AI, equip advocates with

00:15:03.440 --> 00:15:10.080
research to bolster their campaigns, and to build the voice and the choice of the most

00:15:10.080 --> 00:15:11.359
impacted communities.

00:15:12.239 --> 00:15:18.479
They galvanize policymakers, researchers, industry practitioners to mitigate AI bias

00:15:18.479 --> 00:15:18.960
and harm.

00:15:21.200 --> 00:15:29.840
And, of course, the last organization is the Carpentries because, yes, we are the leading

00:15:29.840 --> 00:15:32.960
inclusive community teaching data and coding skills.

00:15:33.039 --> 00:15:39.440
We were founded to teach foundational computation and data science skills through short, impactful

00:15:39.440 --> 00:15:42.640
workshops, and our model is to train the trainer.

00:15:42.640 --> 00:15:48.000
We certify volunteer instructors, and they go out into the communities where they can

00:15:48.000 --> 00:15:50.960
reach people directly with these data skills.

00:15:51.760 --> 00:15:53.760
Our course material is open source.

00:15:53.760 --> 00:15:54.880
It's free to use.

00:15:54.880 --> 00:16:00.000
It's free to contribute to, and in this way, we're able to scale beyond our organization

00:16:00.000 --> 00:16:02.880
and build regional, self-sustaining learning communities.

